commit.message:
Refactor type system to use generated and modular types

Replaces custom and Prisma-based type definitions with generated types from '@/generated/models' and new modular type files in 'src/lib/types'. Updates all components and data functions to use these new types, removes redundant type declarations, and deletes the old 'prisma.ts' and 'data.ts' type files. This improves type safety, maintainability, and consistency across the codebase.

Refactor admin APIs to server actions and update client usage

Replaces admin API routes for orders, metrics, products, and blob deletion with server actions. Updates all affected client components to use the new server actions instead of fetch calls. Refactors seed scripts to write metrics directly to the database. Removes now-unnecessary API route files and cleans up related code.

Refactor API routes to server actions and clean up

Replaces API route handlers for users, collections, newsletter, and orders with server action modules. Removes now-unneeded API route files and migrates all business logic to server actions for admin and user operations, newsletter subscription, and order management. Updates related imports and usage to support the new server action structure.

Refactor cart actions to use server actions and add batch support

Replaces API route calls in cart-related components with direct server action calls for updating, removing, and clearing cart items. Adds new server actions for batch adding items to the cart and fetching the current cart. Refactors cart logic to apply price multipliers consistently and improves error handling. Updates AddAllToCartButton and ReorderButton to use the new batchAddToCartAction.

fix build issue

make sure to run npm install before commit

Add order timeline component and admin order status API

Introduces a new OrderTimeline component for visualizing order progress in the order history page. Adds an admin API route to update order status. Updates the order detail page to use the timeline and improves messaging. Sets up Husky and lint-staged for pre-commit checks, and updates dependencies to support these tools.

Refactor pricing to support market-priced items

Removes the 'total' column from the Order model and database, making product and order item prices nullable to support market-based pricing. Updates all related backend and frontend logic to calculate totals on the fly, handle null (market) prices, and display appropriate warnings and indicators in cart and checkout flows. Adds admin UI for editing market-priced order items, and updates API endpoints, seed scripts, and type definitions accordingly.

Refactor cart retrieval to avoid auto-creation

Introduces a new getCart function to fetch the user's cart without creating one if it doesn't exist, and updates all relevant usages to prevent ghost cart creation. getOrCreateCart is now only used when a cart should be created if missing. Also ensures the most recent cart is always selected by ordering by createdAt descending.

Add product soft delete and order item snapshots

Implements soft delete for products by adding a deletedAt field and index. Adds productNameSnapshot and productImageSnapshot fields to OrderItem for historical accuracy. Updates order placement to capture product snapshots, and updates UI components to use snapshot data if available. Adds order cancellation and conversion back to cart, including new API and UI for cancel/modify actions. Refactors admin and site components for improved navigation and type safety.
Move email and phone fields from Order to Address

Rename inspirationText to text in Inspiration model

Renames the 'inspirationText' field to 'text' in the Prisma Inspiration model and updates all related application code, seed data, API routes, and forms to use the new field name. Includes a database migration to rename the column and ensures consistency across the codebase.

Refactor to use server actions for cart, products, collections, and search

Introduces server actions for cart, collections, inspirations, products, and search, replacing client-side API calls with direct server actions. Updates related components (AddToCartButton, CollectionsTableRow, InspirationForm, NavSearch) to use these actions with React's useTransition for improved UX and error handling. Removes legacy unauthorized admin page and cleans up Hero component props. Also updates dependencies in package.json.
Move user fetching into Nav component

Refactor user type to SessionUser across components

Replaces various ad-hoc user type definitions with a unified SessionUser type imported from src/lib/types/prisma throughout the app and components. Updates getCurrentUser and getOrCreateCart to use SessionUser, and cleans up related props and interfaces for consistency. Also restores several previously commented-out components and removes the outdated REQUIREMENTS.md file.

Move phone field from User to Address model

Refactors the data model to store phone numbers on the Address entity instead of the User. Updates all relevant API routes, forms, validation, and UI components to require and display phone numbers per address. Removes phone editing from user profile, enforces phone as required for addresses, and updates seed data and migration scripts accordingly. Also includes minor UI improvements and refactors destructive button variants.

Refactor UI primitives and update dependencies

Replaced usage of the Button component's `asChild` API with the new `render` prop in documentation and codebase for improved clarity and consistency. Updated dependencies in package.json and package-lock.json, removing unused packages and adding new ones as needed. Added new UI primitive `autocomplete.tsx` and removed deprecated `command.tsx` component. Updated components and documentation to align with new UI conventions.

Refactor theme system and remove ThemeProvider

Replaces the custom theme context and ThemeProvider with a simplified approach, removing related components and context files. Updates Tailwind base color from 'slate' to 'gray' and adds new menu color settings. Adds a postinstall script and updates dependencies, including new UI and utility packages.

Add theme support and refactor color usage

Introduces a ThemeProvider and ThemeToggle for light/dark mode support, updates global CSS variables for theme handling, and replaces hardcoded 'bg-white' classes with 'bg-background' throughout the app. Also refactors several components to use generated model types and improves sign-in flow to use Google social login. Minor UI adjustments include border styling and removal of unused elements.

Remove product variants and add price to Product

Refactored database schema and application logic to eliminate the ProductVariant model. The Product model now includes a price field, and all references to product variants have been removed from code, API routes, and seed scripts. Product associations and pricing now use the Product directly, simplifying data access and reducing complexity.

Add phone number support to user profiles

Introduces phone number support for users by updating the Prisma schema, adding a migration, and implementing phone validation and formatting using libphonenumber-js. Updates account and profile pages to handle phone numbers, adds new UI components for account management, and updates related API routes and validation logic.

Remove email change and billing address features

Eliminates support for changing user email addresses and related verification logic; email is now managed exclusively via Google OAuth and cannot be changed. Removes billing address references from order APIs and admin UI. Updates dependencies, refines product controls, and improves signup/signin flows to use Google authentication only. Adds idToken to Account model for future OAuth support.
Remove billing address since we don't use payments
Add a new product type of roses

Add market price support for product variants

Introduces an isMarketPrice field to ProductVariant, updates generated types and enums, and clarifies payment terms in legal and FAQ pages. Cart UI now shows free shipping, and cart item links are visually improved. Also adds a new product type (roses) to TODO and a new Prisma migration script to package.json.

Enable product management in collections and inspiration

Adds product selection to the admin collection form and API routes, allowing products to be managed within collections. Refactors the inspiration detail page to support interactive quantity selection and a new product table component, improving user experience when adding sets to cart. Shop filters now visually indicate active filters, and minor UI improvements were made to search and filter components.

Remove dynamic hero banners and related admin features

Eliminates the HeroBanner model, API routes, admin pages, and validation logic for dynamic hero banners. Replaces dynamic hero banners with static components for homepage hero sections. Cleans up related Prisma schema, seed data, and generated types. Updates admin sidebar to remove hero management link.

Add tracked DB client and improve metrics system

Introduces a tracked Prisma client for admin and user query metrics, refactors metrics storage to use the database instead of in-memory, and updates all admin pages to use tracked DB access. Adds new metric types (ADMIN_QUERY, USER_QUERY), updates metrics API to be async, and removes the seed metrics page and sidebar link. Also updates the cookies page for clarity and adds a shipping banner to the cart page.

Update image paths and rename asset folders

Standardized image paths in seed data and Cart component to use /categories and /products directories instead of /featured-categories and /featured-products. Renamed and moved image assets accordingly for better organization. Updated peakblooms logo image.

Add admin content management and API endpoints

Introduces admin pages for managing products, categories, and collections, including create, edit, and list views. Adds API routes for CRUD operations on products, categories, and inspiration sets (collections). Updates the admin dashboard to provide access to new management sections. Refactors authentication checks and improves UI components for inline editing and management actions. Minor UI improvements to sign-in and sign-up forms.

Add cart UI with variant selection and API updates

Implements a full shopping cart UI with quantity and variant selection, including optimistic updates and debounced API calls. Adds a new API route to fetch product variants, updates the cart item PATCH API to support variant changes, and adjusts cart count logic to count unique items. Also introduces a reusable debounced callback hook and improves admin navigation and shop filter UI.

Refactor auth, cart, and UI for server-side logic and UX

Migrates authentication and authorization checks in cart and orders pages to server-side redirects for improved security and SSR. Adds cart count badge to navigation, refactors product card to show pricing/specs per user state, and updates add-to-cart buttons to use toast notifications and router methods. Shop filters now fetch options server-side and display as a horizontal bar on desktop. Adds badge UI component and documents app requirements and standards.

Update branding and improve shop/filter UI

Updated page metadata titles to 'Peak Blooms' branding and improved shop layout with sidebar filters. Refined ProductConfigurator sign-in messaging and streamlined ShopFilters desktop UI. Updated favicon and logo assets.

Refactor shop page and filters to use server-side data and Radix UI Label

Migrates the shop page to server-side data fetching with Prisma, replacing client-side hooks and API calls. Updates ShopFilters to use the new Label component from Radix UI, improves filter value handling, and adjusts Select component styles for consistency. Adds a reusable Label UI component and refines Select UI styles.

Add 'use client' directive to ProductConfigurator

Added the 'use client' directive to ProductConfigurator.tsx to ensure it is treated as a client component. Also removed unused imports from shop/[slug]/page.tsx for code cleanup.

Add product filtering by color, stem length, and price

Introduces filtering options for products by color, stem length, and price in the shop page and API. Adds a new ShopFilters component, updates Prisma schema and migration to support color, and refactors product API routes to handle new filter parameters.

Add product image preview to inspiration table

Introduces a new 'Image' column to the products table on inspiration pages, displaying a small preview image for each product or a placeholder if no image is available. Also updates TODO.md to reflect progress and new tasks.

Refactor admin user management to use server components

Migrates admin user listing and authorization checks to server components, fetching users directly from the database. Extracts user card UI into ApprovedUserCard and PendingUserCard components for better separation of concerns. Updates redirect logic for admin routes and simplifies approval/rejection flows.

Add admin navigation with settings icon for admins

Introduces an admin link in the navigation bar for users with the ADMIN role, using a new IconSettings component. Updates icon exports to include IconSettings and removes a completed admin redirect TODO.

Improve admin access flow and session handling

Adds a server-side redirect handler for admin users after sign-in, refines unauthorized admin page to show different actions for signed-in and unsigned users, and ensures session data is refreshed from the database for accurate role and approval status. Removes unused proxy middleware and updates layout and page containers for consistency.

Update collection button text to 'View Collection'

Changed button label from 'Shop Now' to 'View Collection' in both collections page and featured collections component for improved clarity. Also removed user authentication item from TODO.md.

Update user param handling and Nav user email type

Changed RouteParams to accept a Promise for params and updated PATCH handler to await params for user ID extraction. Also modified NavProps to allow user email to be null, improving type safety.

Remove product and variant stock fields, add batch cart API

Eliminates the 'stock' field from Product and ProductVariant models, updates related seed and API logic, and introduces a new /api/cart/batch endpoint for adding multiple items to the cart at once. Adds AddAllToCartButton component and updates inspiration set page to support batch cart addition. Cleans up related UI and API code to reflect the removal of stock and support for product variants in cart operations.

Refactor user status handling to use server-side user

Replaces the useUserStatus client hook with server-side user retrieval via getCurrentUser. Updates components and pages to accept user props and removes the useUserStatus hook. This change improves consistency and enables user-dependent rendering on the server.

Enforce approval for cart and orders, add user status hook

Shopping cart and orders API routes now require user approval. Added useUserStatus hook for client-side user status checks. Updated components and pages to use approval logic, removed price visibility checks from server components, and integrated sonner for notifications. Deleted obsolete documentation files.

Rename middleware.ts to proxy.ts and update export

Renamed the file from middleware.ts to proxy.ts and changed the exported function name from middleware to proxy for clarity and consistency.

Add account signup and pending approval flow

Introduces a new user signup page and a pending approval page, including a resend confirmation email feature with supporting API and component. Updates navigation to include sign up, refines cart visibility for authenticated users, and improves footer and inspiration set layouts. Removes related links from product detail page and updates icon set.

Add admin dashboard, user management, and auth integration

Introduces admin dashboard and user management pages with approval workflow. Adds API routes for admin user listing and approval/rejection, integrates NextAuth for authentication and session management, and updates navigation and product card components to reflect user roles and approval status. Also adds middleware for admin route protection and improves footer links.

Add ProductVariant model and update schema

Introduces a ProductVariant model to support product variants with price, stem length, count per bunch, and stock. Updates CartItem and OrderItem to reference product variants, modifies migration and schema files, and adds @radix-ui/react-select dependency for UI enhancements.

Add inspiration sets feature and hero background

Introduces a new 'FeaturedInInspirationSets' component to display related inspiration sets on the product detail page. Updates the Hero component to use a slate green flowers background image for improved aesthetics. Removes the stock status and back button from the product page. Updates the style guide with new color scheme values.

Remove FeaturedInspiration from homepage

The FeaturedInspiration component import and usage have been removed from the Home page. This streamlines the homepage content and may be part of a redesign or simplification effort.

Replace Twitter and Gallery icons with Rose icon

Removed Twitter icon and related link from Footer. Replaced Gallery icon with Rose icon for the Inspiration link in Nav and updated icon exports accordingly.

Update homepage hero text for clarity

Revised the hero section title and subtitle on the homepage to better communicate the business offering. Also added a new shop page filtering feature to the TODO list.

Add shop pages and refactor product card usage

Introduced new shop listing and product detail pages. Refactored product card UI into a reusable ProductCard component, updating collection and featured products to use it. Adjusted price visibility logic based on user authentication and approval status. Minor UI tweaks to inspiration page image aspect ratio.

Add description to Category model and collections pages

Introduces a 'description' field to the Category model in Prisma and updates related API, seed, and generated types. Adds new collections pages to display categories and their products, and updates UI components to use category descriptions. Also includes minor UI improvements for inspiration pages.

Add InspirationSet model and migrate to dynamic data

Introduces the InspirationSet model and migration in Prisma, updates seed data to include inspiration sets, and refactors frontend components to fetch categories, products, and inspiration sets from the database instead of static data. Removes unused generated Prisma files and updates .gitignore to exclude the entire /src/generated directory. Adds Prisma generate to postinstall and configures Prisma seed in package.json.

Add override for @auth/core to version 0.41.1

Added an 'overrides' section in package.json to enforce @auth/core version 0.41.1. This ensures consistent dependency resolution and addresses potential issues with mismatched versions in the project.

Update next-auth to v5 and fix cart item route params

Upgraded next-auth to version 5.0.0-beta.30 and added nodemailer as a dependency. Refactored cart item PATCH and DELETE API routes to handle async params and fixed usage of id extraction. Removed unnecessary ts-expect-error comment in auth session callback.

Update logo image sizing in Footer and Nav

Adjusted the Peak Blooms logo image dimensions and styling in both Footer and Nav components for improved appearance and consistency. Added custom height and width classes, and set eager loading for the Nav logo.

Add Prisma seed script and update DB integration

Introduced prisma/seed.ts for seeding the database and updated prisma.config.ts for new Prisma configuration. Refactored FeaturedCollections and FeaturedProducts components to fetch data from the database instead of static sources. Updated db.ts for new Prisma client usage. Added relevant dependencies for PostgreSQL and Prisma in package.json.

Add Prisma database, NextAuth, and API endpoints

Introduced Prisma ORM with full schema and migrations, NextAuth.js authentication with Resend email integration, and REST API routes for products, categories, user profiles, shopping cart, and orders. Added supporting documentation, utility functions, and updated dependencies in package.json. Updated .gitignore and cleaned up TODO.md.

Add serif font and update branding elements

Introduces Playfair Display as a serif font for elegant headings and applies it to key components. Updates social media links in the footer to use actual Peak Blooms profiles. Adds a custom logo image to the navigation bar, improves image loading with responsive sizes, and refines some text and layout details for consistency.

Update navigation links and color variables

Replaces 'About' and 'Contact' links with 'Collections' in the navigation, updates associated icons, and adjusts CSS color variables for primary and secondary elements. Also refines NavLink button hover styles for improved UI consistency.

Update site metadata for branding

Changed the site title and description in metadata to reflect Peak Blooms branding and provide a more descriptive summary for florist businesses.

Add inspiration sets feature and navigation

Introduces 'Inspirational Sets' with new pages for listing and viewing details of curated flower arrangements. Adds FeaturedInspiration component, AddToCartButton, and updates navigation to include Inspiration. Removes FeaturedCategories and updates the home page to showcase inspirational sets.

Add footer and featured categories components

Introduces a new Footer component and integrates it into the main layout. Adds a FeaturedCategories component for displaying curated flower collections. Updates FeaturedProducts subtitles for brevity and expands icon support with social media icons. Documents the decision to use a single light theme in the style guide.

Refactor to use rounded-xs for card and button corners

Introduces a new .rounded-xs utility for extra-small border radius in globals.css and updates all relevant components (FeaturedProducts, FeaturedCollections, and button variants) to use rounded-xs instead of rounded-sm/rounded-lg. Renames FeaturedCategories to FeaturedCollections and updates references and content accordingly for consistency with site terminology.

Add FeaturedProducts component and images

Introduces a new FeaturedProducts component displaying handpicked products with images and links. Updates the home page to use this component and adds four product images to the public directory.

Add featured categories section and images

Introduces a new FeaturedCategories component with three curated flower categories and associated images. Removes unused SVG files, updates the home page to display featured categories, and adds an ArrowRight icon to the UI icons module.

Refactor accent color usage to primary/secondary

Replaces 'accent' color variables and classes with 'primary' and 'secondary' throughout global styles and components. Updates Hero component to accept a ReactNode for CTA, allowing more flexible button rendering. This improves color consistency and simplifies theme management.

Add Hero component and gradient styles

Introduces a reusable Hero component for the site landing section, including a new radial gradient background utility and related CSS variables. Updates the home page to use the Hero component and adds a flower icon to the UI icon set.

Refactor UI controls to use shared Button component

Replaced custom and native button/link elements with the shared Button primitive across navigation and main page components for consistent styling and accessibility. Updated documentation to enforce Button usage for all interactive controls. Simplified button implementation and removed unused icon props. Minor style guide and CSS cleanup.

Add centralized icon system and integrate across UI

Introduces a new icons helper file re-exporting lucide-react icons with consistent sizing. Updates navigation, buttons, and CTA links to use these icons for improved affordance and visual hierarchy. Enhances accessibility and maintains a clean, modern aesthetic as documented in the style guide.

Add navigation bar and improve homepage layout

Introduces a responsive navigation bar with links and active state highlighting via new Nav and NavLink components. Updates layout.tsx to include the navigation and refactors page.tsx to enhance the homepage with a welcome section and call-to-action buttons. Cleans up README by removing extra documentation and deployment instructions.

Add documentation and update project overview

Added functional requirements and style guide documents to the docs directory. Updated README with project details, features, and tech stack. Modified next.config.ts to disable devIndicators. Simplified the home page by removing template content and placeholder UI.

Add UI button component and utility functions

Introduces a reusable Button component with multiple variants and sizes using class-variance-authority and Radix UI Slot. Adds a utility function for merging Tailwind and clsx classes. Updates globals.css for new color variables, theme support, and animation imports. Adds required dependencies and configuration for UI components.
Initial commit from Create Next App
